## Scoring Modes
Tests are scored in two modes:
- **Batch** — uses `stretch_buffer()` (full-file processing). This is the traditional code path through `src/stretch/hybrid.rs`.
- **Streaming** — uses `StreamProcessor` with hybrid mode enabled (chunked real-time processing). This code path lives in `src/stream/processor.rs`.

If streaming scores lag behind batch scores, look at `src/stream/processor.rs` for phase vocoder state management, ring buffer handling, or hybrid mode transitions. Both modes share the underlying WSOLA and phase vocoder engines, but streaming adds chunked buffering and ratio smoothing.

